<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1910,2006]" lastBlockId="8.[151,1436,151,968]" lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[197,364,1946,1970]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">Male genitalia</emphasis>
: Pygofer triangularly produced caudally with dorsal marginal mesal plate-like lobe as in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divaricatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="48">P. divaricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; macrosetae in caudal half and along dorsal margin at midlength area. Subgenital plates rounded with even lateral margins, anterior extension directed dorsally. Style with rounded distal margin. Connective V-shaped, dorsally directed. Aedeagus with dorsal apodeme poorly developed, base stout with one pair of filamentous unpigmented sinuate processes at base of short tubular shaft, twice as long as shaft and one pair of blade-like caudally narrowed ventral processes almost three times as long as shaft. Gonopore apical.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis box="[197,396,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
