<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="49" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,584,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[708,790,583,607]" name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
by Matsumura (
<number box="[983,1043,583,607]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="1914.0">1914</number>
), based on four female specimens that are deposited in Hokkaido University, 
<collectingCountry box="[630,697,621,644]" name="Japan" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Japan</collectingCountry>
. Later, Metcalf (
<number box="[881,939,620,644]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="1957.0">1957</number>
) transferred 
<taxonomicName authority="Matsumura" authorityName="Matsumura" box="[1082,1435,620,644]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis box="[1082,1302,620,644]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Parallygus guttatus</emphasis>
Matsumura
</taxonomicName>
to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[292,401,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Phlepsius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[292,401,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Phlepsius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
without explanation. Photos of 
<typeStatus box="[758,806,656,680]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">type</typeStatus>
specimen of 
<taxonomicName box="[956,1073,657,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis box="[956,1073,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">P. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with label data “ 
<collectingCountry box="[1262,1349,655,679]" name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, Shirin, 
<date box="[151,300,692,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="1906-07-31">
<number box="[151,179,692,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="31.0">31</number>
July 
<number box="[241,300,692,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="1906.0">1906</number>
</date>
, Nitobe I., 
<taxonomicName box="[427,648,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis box="[427,648,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Parallygus guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
det. Matsumura”, are available on the website of the National Digital Archives Program/ National Museum of Natural Science (
<collectionCode box="[802,886,727,751]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/2nry-s1yg" name="National Museum of Natural Science" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">NMNS</collectionCode>
) (
<number box="[909,969,727,751]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="2011.0">2011</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
The identity of the male genitalia of this species is tentative as it is based on specimens from mainland 
<collectingCountry box="[1369,1436,764,788]" name="China" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">China</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[199,260,799,823]" name="India" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">India</collectingCountry>
. This somewhat wide distribution (
<figureCitation box="[658,725,799,823]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1587,1610]" captionTargetBox="[154,1432,193,1565]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[154,1433,193,1566]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Map showing distribution of species of Parallygus in India, Sri Lanka and China." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210591/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[711,725,799,823]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="8.0">8</number>
</figureCitation>
) together with the similarity of these specimens to the original description and photos of 
<taxonomicName box="[444,562,837,860]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis box="[444,562,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">P. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, suggests that they are conspecific with the specimens (
<taxonomicName box="[1194,1312,837,860]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="guttatus">
<emphasis box="[1194,1312,837,860]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">P. guttatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) from 
<collectingCountry name="Taiwan" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,968]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
This species is closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[572,727,908,932]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Parallygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divaricatus">
<emphasis box="[572,727,908,932]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">P. divaricatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differing only in having a straight ventral process (
<figureCitation box="[1312,1378,908,932]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1787,1810]" captionTargetBox="[216,1385,392,1740]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[188,1398,362,1766]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Parallygus guttatus Matsumura, specimen from India. A. Forewing venation; B. Male genital capsule; C. Pygofer process, dorsal view; D. Subgenital plate, lateral view; E. Style, dorsal view; F. Aedeagus, lateral view; G. Aedeagus, posteroventral view; H. Connective, anterior-ventral view; I. Subgenital plates and styles, dorsal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210588/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1365,1378,908,932]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="5.0">5</number>
</figureCitation>
F) of the aedeagus compared to distally strongly curved ventral process in the latter (
<figureCitation box="[1038,1106,943,967]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1598,1621]" captionTargetBox="[237,1357,228,1545]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[191,1395,193,1577]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Parallygus divaricatus Melichar. A. Male genital capsule; B. Pygofer process, ventral view; C. Connective, anteroventral view; D. Sclerotized bridge across pygofer lobes, posterior view; E. Style and connective, posterodorsal view; F. Aedeagus, lateral view. Free hand diagrams not to scale." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/210587/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="49">
Fig. 
<number box="[1090,1106,943,967]" pageId="8" pageNumber="49" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
F).
</paragraph>
